{"name": "simple-cisco-support-api", "metadata": {"name": "simple-cisco-support-api", "version": "0.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Topic :: System :: Installation/Setup", "Topic :: System :: Systems Administration", "Topic :: Utilities"], "home_page": "https://github.com/jinjamator/simple_cisco_support_api", "license": "ASL V2", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["httpx"], "summary": "Simple REST-client for Cisco Support API", "upload_time": 1733216235}, "documentation": ["# Introduction\n\nsimple_cisco_support_api is a simplified REST Client for the Cisco Support API\n\n## Features\n\nsimple_cisco_support_api has following features:\n: - manage login\n  - CRUD interface for all possible API URLs\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall simple_cisco_support_api by running:\n\n```bash\npip3 install simple_cisco_support_api\n```\n\n## Examples\n\n### Get Infos For A Specific Bug\n\n```python\nimport getpass\nfrom simple_cisco_support_api import CiscoSupportAPIClient\nfrom pprint import pprint\n\ncisco_support=CiscoSupportAPIClient()\ncisco_support.login(input(\"client_id:\"),getpass.getpass(\"client_secret:\"))\npprint(cisco_support.api.bug('v3.0').bugs.bug_ids.CSCwc66053.get())\n```\n\n## Contribute\n\n- Issue Tracker: <https://github.com/jinjamator/simple_cisco_support_api/issues>\n- Source Code: <https://github.com/jinjamator/simple_cisco_support_api>\n\n## Roadmap\n\nSelected Roadmap items:\n: - add more documentation\n  - add some more examples\n\nFor documentation please refer to <https://simple_cisco_support_api.readthedocs.io/en/latest/>\n\n## License\n\nThis project is licensed under the Apache License Version 2.0\n"], "modules": [{"name": "simple_cisco_support_api.rest_client", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "simple_cisco_support_api.rest_client.exceptions", "documentation"